40|$|This study investigates capital {{structure}} around 286 self-tender offers from 1980 to 1997. Firms that undertake self-tender offers generally have debt ratios below their predicted levels before the offers. The debt ratios following nondefensive self-tender offers {{are close to}} predicted levels, while the ratios following defensive self-tender offers are above predicted levels. Further, 20 % and 43 % of the debt ratings are downgraded following nondefensive and defensive self-tender offers, respectively. Finally, the <b>increases</b> <b>in</b> <b>debt</b> ratios around the offers are negatively related to the difference from the predicted debt ratio before the offers. ...|$|R
